Yesss it’s #BlackInPhysics week!! Get ready!! 

My name is Arianna 👋🏾 I started off in math education @TowsonU, fell in love with astrophysics so I got my M.S. @CalStateLA. Now I’m a PhD candidate @UCIPhysAstro studying massive dusty galaxy evolution.

@MarieSpiker @TowsonU Congratulations, @MarieSpiker for proposing + organizing this fantastic, interdisciplinary session. It was my pleasure to participate--so much to think about! I like how you are looking at movement of nutrients through these connected systems before they are available to humans.

Jillian Fry @JFry27 of @TowsonU introduced us to the complexity of aquatic foods!

🐟 Many production methods: marine/freshwater, wild/farmed, 100s of species

🐟Sustainability issues: overfishing, bycatch, human rights. Varies widely by species & production method
